A 29-year-old Kaduna-based tailor, Gado Yahaya, was yesterday arraigned before a Kaduna Magistrate Court for allegedly killing his neighbour during an argument over a bucket of water. A resident of Rigasa, the community where the accused resides, said Yahaya allegedly fought with Liman Salisu during an argument over a bucket of water which resulted in Salisu’s death. “He is a resident of Rigasa in Igabi Local Government Area of Kaduna State and was arraigned on charges of culpable homicide before a Kaduna Magistrate Court on Monday.   Wife denies being held hostage by husband     25 suspected Yahoo boys arrested in Ibadan     Hanifa: Kano re-arraigns school proprietor   “The Prosecutor, Insp. Chidi Leo alleged that Yahaya killed Salisu with a pestle during their fight over the bucket of water. “In the course of the fight, he went into the kitchen, picked a pestle and hit  Salisu on his head. He slumped and died on the way to the hospital.” - Advertisement - Chief Magistrate, Ibrahim Emmanuel, ordered that Yahaya be remanded in a correctional facility, adding that the court lacked jurisdiction to hear the matter.   SPONSORED